Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora from neck join to moderate turn. Clay near fine mid orange-brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 80, 31. Name Moschos.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0952)
